        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up on the Hopi reservation, surrounded by Navaho land.  Your family were farmers, and they secretly taught you the traditions of your people when the White Man tried to bleed them away, or when the Navaho ran their herds through your crops.  But though you tried, you could not keep your land.  Your family slowly starved, and in desperation, you stood before your gods, as best you could, and begged for help.  Your sire was interested in the ways that others revered the land, and happened to be passing through the area.  You spoke with him long into the night.  He took you just before the dawn on the land that was your family's no longer, and you studied with him for decades.  His pride was strong when you were invited to join the Cardinal's pack, but you still keep in touch.  There is much left to learn from him."
